body:
I'm trying to boil this down into something I can demonstrate in `test_regress`.  But I am currently getting different C++ from the same inputs, e.g.:
```
    // Init
    VlWide<5>/*149:0*/ __VdfgSynthAssign___PVT__foo_h6e95ff9d_0_7;
    VL_ZERO_W(150, __VdfgSynthAssign___PVT__foo_h6e95ff9d_0_7);
    VlWide<3>/*74:0*/ __VdfgRegularize_h6e95ff9d_0_30;
    VL_ZERO_W(75, __VdfgRegularize_h6e95ff9d_0_30);
    VlWide<5>/*149:0*/ __VdfgRegularize_h6e95ff9d_0_31;
    VL_ZERO_W(150, __VdfgRegularize_h6e95ff9d_0_31);
    VlWide<5>/*159:0*/ __Vtemp_33;
    // Body
```
vs
```
    // Init
    VlWide<5>/*149:0*/ __VdfgSynthAssign___PVT__foo_h6e95ff9d_0_7;
    VL_ZERO_W(150, __VdfgSynthAssign___PVT__foo_h6e95ff9d_0_7);
    VlWide<5>/*149:0*/ __VdfgRegularize_h6e95ff9d_0_30;
    VL_ZERO_W(150, __VdfgRegularize_h6e95ff9d_0_30);
    VlWide<3>/*74:0*/ __VdfgRegularize_h6e95ff9d_0_32;
    VL_ZERO_W(75, __VdfgRegularize_h6e95ff9d_0_32);
    VlWide<5>/*159:0*/ __Vtemp_33;
    // Body
```
The problem here is that these two `__VdfgRegularize` vars get created, named and initialized in different orders from verilation to verilation.  There are other knock-on effects, but I believe this is the root cause.

I took a look at `V3DfgRegularize.cpp` but nothing is immediately jumping out at me as non-deterministic.  All of the looping I can find is on `DfgVertex::List`s which is a `V3List` which should be ordered.

@gezalore any thoughts where I should look?  Also, I'm wondering if this could be an ancillary use for RTLMeter: verilating big designs multiple times and confirming that the results are stable.  Thoughts?

